Sure, here are some example sentences that use the word "verzija" in different forms and positions:

1. *Verzija* programa koji si skinuo je zastarela. (The *version* of the program you downloaded is outdated.)
2. Da li si probao novu *verziju* ove igre? (Have you tried the new *version* of this game?)
3. Želim da vidim *verziju* tvoje prezentacije pre nego što je prezentuješ. (I want to see the *version* of your presentation before you present it.)
4. Ova *verzija* softvera ne radi dobro na starom računaru. (This *version* of the software doesn't work well on an old computer.)
5. *Verzija* koju si mi poslao nije otvorena. (The *version* you sent me won't open.)
6. Pošalji mi najnoviju *verziju* dokumenta. (Send me the latest *version* of the document.)
7. Moramo da napravimo drugu *verziju* ovog spota. (We need to make another *version* of this commercial.)
8. Moja omiljena *verzija* ove pesme je u akustičnoj izvedbi. (My favorite *version* of this song is in an acoustic performance.)
9. *Verzije* ovog programa su dostupne za Windows i Mac. (The *versions* of this program are available for Windows and Mac.)
10. Prvo sam napisala rukom *verziju* ovog eseja, pa sam je prekucala. (I first wrote a handwritten *version* of this essay, then typed it.)

Note: The word "verzija" means "version" in English. I've emphasized it in each sentence with a star (*) for clarity.